modules.description: This module implements HTTP client operations for issuing requests over network endpoints using a context-aware configuration. It supports standard HTTP methods like GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, and PATCH, with options to specify headers, request bodies, and URI targets. The module works with Cohttp types for requests and responses, and uses Lwt for asynchronous execution, making it suitable for building web clients or interacting with HTTP APIs in a MirageOS or Unix-based OCaml application.
